      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Material properties (elastic modulus, Poisson's ratio, yield strength) were sourced from ASTM-certified coupon testing of the same material lot used for the F1717 constructs. Geometric inputs were derived from calibrated CMM measurements of production hardware. Sensitivity analysis confirmed that stiffness QoI varies less than 2% across the measured material property uncertainty range."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Eleven production-representative constructs (N=6 Lab 1, N=5 Lab 2) were assembled from components drawn from the same production lot as the device under submission. Dimensional inspection confirmed all samples within nominal tolerance. Sample size provides statistical power sufficient to estimate mean QoI within ±8% at 95% confidence."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted under a single load configuration (ASTM F1717 compression-bending at 5 mm/min crosshead speed, ambient temperature). Variation in loading rate and temperature was not explored. This limits generalizability to conditions outside the standard protocol and yields only Gradation 1 for this factor, which is below the required level of 2. This known gap is acknowledged in the submission."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
