    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The FEA modeling framework for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct meets or exceeds the required credibility level for 12 of 13 V&V 40 factors. The single below-requirement factor (Test conditions, Gradation 1 vs. required 2) is acknowledged and accepted given the regulatory standing of the ASTM F1717 protocol as the standard evaluation method. The not-assessed factor (Relevance of the validation activities to the COU) is considered beyond scope for this submission phase and is flagged for resolution in a subsequent assessment; it does not alter the overall Accepted determination given the strength of the quantitative validation evidence and the well-established regulatory acceptance of F1717 as a surrogate for clinical performance.",
